<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Beats Slovakia to Win ITF Junior Team Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Lina Krasnoroutskaia's powerful
play led Russia to a 2-1 victory over defending champions Slovakia
in the girls' final at the ITF team tennis tournament in Nagoya of
Japan on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Krasnoroutskaia smashed aside Daniela Hantuchova 6-2, 6-4 in
the opener and Elena Bovina ensured a unbeatable 2-0 lead by
beating Martina Babakova 6-4, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
But the Russians failed to perfect their victory as
Krasnoroutskaia and Galina Fokina lost to Hantuchova and Lubomira
Kurhaicova in the dead rubber 2-6, 6-2, 2-6.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time that Russia have won the girls' team
title in the under-14 tournament.
</P>
<P>
Argentina crashed Croatia 3-0 to finished third on the final
standings.
</P>
<P>
The boys' final will be played Sunday between South Africa and
the Czech Republic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
