<HEADLINE> China Demands Early Release of Detained Fishermen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 23 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese diplomat met with
the Philippine consul-general in Hong Kong this morning and
demanded an early release of the Chinese fishermen and the boat
detained by Philippine authorities, an official spokesman said
here today.
</P>
<P>
In an urgent meeting with Philippine Consul-general Estrella
Berenuel, Jiang Changshi, director of the Consular Department of
the Office of the Chinese Foreign Ministry's Commissioner in Hong
Kong, said that the fishermen and the boat have been detained
for more than three weeks.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine side had offered to deal with the issue as soon
as possible, but has so far failed to solve it in a proper way,
Dai noted, adding that the Chinese side has expressed its deep
regret over this.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong-registered fishing boat was detained by the
Philippines in the South China Sea on July 31, with 23 fishermen
aboard, including three Hong Kong residents.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese official hoped that the Philippine side will not
make the issue a complicated one and urged an early release of
both the crew and the boat.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine consul-general said that he will report to his
government immediately. 
</P>
</TEXT>
