<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier entertained by Malaysia's Pinang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PULAU PINANG, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Chief Minister of Pinang
State of Malaysia Koh Tsu Koon hosted a banquet here tonight to
entertain visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng and his wife Zhu Lin.
</P>
<P>
During the banquet, Li Peng was entertained by Malaysian
artists with traditional Malay songs and dances.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Deputy Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim attended
tonight's banquet.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier and his entourage arrived here this morning
after a visit to Kuala Lumpur where he held talks with his
Malaysian counterpart Mahathir Mohammad on bilateral relations and
on international and regional issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Li Peng visited Penang industry development
zone, Motorola Malaysia and inspected Teluk Pahang dam project
being constructed by a Chinese company here.  
</P>
