<HEADLINE> Beijing Reception to Honor Tibetan Study Scholars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Ngapoi Ngawang Jigme,
vice-chairman of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) National Committee, hosted a reception to mark
the end of '97 Beijing Seminar on Tibetan Studies and honor all
Chinese and foreign experts and scholars attending the seminar.
</P>
<P>
He said Tibet have witnessed profound changes in all
respects and that a thriving situation has emerged in the Tibetan
Studies thanks to stable social situation and thriving economy in
the autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that the Communist Party of China and the central
government have attached importance to any progress made in
Tibet. Both late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping and President Jiang
Zemin have shown kind attention to the Tibetan people.
</P>
<P>
He exprseed the hope all participants at the seminar to witness
a real, objective and thriving Tibet and personally experience the
pulse of its development during their following trip to Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, He hoped that the seminar could lay a solid basis for
the future researches and academic exchanges in this field.
</P>
<P>
At the four-day seminar that ended here today, some 130
participants presented theses on a variety of topics on Tibetan
society, economy, history, culture and language, in addition to a
profound and wide-ranging exchange of views.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
