<HEADLINE> Kong and Deng Sweep Malaysian Table Tennis Open Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 24 (Xinhua) -- China's top seeds Kong
Linghui and Deng Yaping easily swept the men's and women's singles
titles at the Malaysian Open table tennis championships here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kong, former world champion, beat Saire Jean-Michel of Belgium
21-11, 21-15, 21-15 in 28 minutes to take 9,000 dollars, while the
three-time world champion Deng beat compatriot Yang Ying 21-14,
15-21, 21-14, 21-19 to receive the cash award of 6,000 dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the men's doubles final, Chinese pair Ma Lin and Yan Sen
pushed aside compatriots Kong Ling Hui and Liu Gao Zheng 21-17,
21-17 to grab the 3,000 dollar prize money.
</P>
<P>
But in the women's doubles final, South Korean pair, Park
Hae-Jung and Kim Moo-Kyo beat Chinese Deng Yaping and Yang Yang
19-21,21-13, 21-14.
</P>
<P>
The 45,000 dollars championships attracted participants from
China, Austria, China's Hong Kong, Canada, South Korea and
Malaysia. 
</P>
