<HEADLINE> Kuwait Condemns Israeli Attacks Against Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait today strongly
condemned Israel for its latest bombardment against Lebanese
targets and urged the international community to take immediate
measures to stop the military operations on civilians and revive
the deadlocked Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti Minister of State for Cabinet Affairs Abdul Aziz
Al-Dakhil made the condemnation after a weekly cabinet meeting
here.
</P>
<P>
"The cabinet is following up with concern the continuous
Israeli barbaric attacks against Lebanon and the random shelling
targeting civilian areas," said Al-Dakhil.
</P>
<P>
Israeli warplanes fired at least six air-to-surface missiles at
the position of Hezbollah guerrillas in the western sector of the
border enclave Saturday in south Lebanon as part of a series of
attacks last week on targets in areas of south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Nine civilians were reportedly killed and 41 wounded in south
Lebanon's provincial capital Saida when the pro-Israeli South
Lebanon Army militia opened heavy artillery fire against the city
last Monday.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon and Israel have been exchanging accusations over
violation of the April 1996 cease-fire agreement which banned
both sides from targeting civilians or launching attacks from
civilian areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
