<HEADLINE> Pakistan's Share in World Exports Just 0.18 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's share in world
exports has remained unchanged at 0.18 percent during the five
year period of 1991-1995 mainly because of decline in exports of
manufactured goods, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate of the country's exports during this period was
only 2.1 percent as the exports increased from 6.4 billion U.S.
dollars in 1991 to 8.1 billion in 1995, the statistics said.
</P>
<P>
The decline is observed in exports from the major sectors
including textile and clothing, carpets and carpeting, leather and
leather goods, the statistics said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
