<HEADLINE> Beijing's Hi-Tech Zone Witnesses Investment Upsurge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The continuing influx of
investment is expected to transform the Beijing Economic and
Technological Development Zone into a modern base for new
high-tech industries and promote an export-oriented economy.
</P>
<P>
Some 166 ventures have located in the zone over the past five
years, with total investments standing at 1.06 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Twenty multinationals have accounted for 60 percent of the
total, with high-tech enterprises related to electronics,
bioengineering, and pharmaceuticals holding the dominant position.
</P>
<P>
Liang Yuewen, general manager of the zone's development
company, said that top priority has been granted to high-tech
ventures in order to give full play to the capital city's
technological advantages.
</P>
<P>
The zone has already attracted a large group of related
enterprises and the developer plans to establish a high-tech
industrial belt to attract more talented technicians and
accelerate technological development.
</P>
<P>
A favorable environment, complete infrastructure facilities,
developed communications network and service industry, as well as
frequent overseas trade contacts have greatly sharpened the zone's
competitive edge for attracting investment.
</P>
<P>
The development zone yielded 174 million yuan in total output
value for the first half this year, a 1.26-fold increase on last
year's same period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
