<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Offshore Oil Sector Develops Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- China has verified offshore
geological oil and gas reserves totaling 1.46 billion tons and 320
billion cu m, respectively, with 19 oil and gas fields currently
in operation.
</P>
<P>
According to a senior official with the China National Offshore
Oil Corp. (CNOOC), a 15 year effort has enabled the nation to
developed the world's most advanced technology and equipment for
offshore oil exploration.
</P>
<P>
China's annual offshore crude oil output has jumped from less
than 100,000 tons in 1982 to the present 15 million tons, with the
nation's annual offshore gas output topping 2.6 billion cubic
meters.
</P>
<P>
CNOOC has attempted to enhance offshore oil development by
inking 126 contracts and agreements, valued at over 5.4 billion US
dollars, with 67 oil companies from 18 countries and regions.
</P>
</TEXT>
