<HEADLINE> China's Largest Offshore Oil Field in Bohai Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Shengli Oilfield, China's
second largest, has recorded a major breakthrough in oil
exploration by developing the Chengdao Oilfield in the Bohai Sea
off the nation's east coast.
</P>
<P>
The new oilfield, which has an annual output of 1.05 million
tons and is the largest offshore oil field in the Bohai Bay, offer
massive production potential.
</P>
<P>
According to an official from the China National Petroleum Corp.
(CNPC), exploration of the offshore oilfield was difficult due to
its complicated geological structure. Shengli has developed
Chengdao by applying a vast array of new technology for onshore
development, including 3-D seismic surveys and oil reserve
tracking technology.
</P>
<P>
The Bohai area has an respective annual oil and gas outputs of
2.12 million tons and 367 million cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
Oil officials expect even greater progress this year in oil and
gas exploration in the Bohai area, with forecasts calling for
proven oil and gas reserves forecast to hit 60 million tons and 10
billion cu. m. respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
