<HEADLINE> Trinidad Retains IBF Super-Welterweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Defending IBF
super-welterweight world champion Felix Trinidad of Puerto Rico
beat Australian Troy Waters to retain his title at Madison Square
Gardnes of New York on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
Trinidad needed less three minutes to fend off the challenge
from the 32-year-old Waters.
</P>
<P>
"I came here to win by KO," said Trinidad, who now hopes to
challenge WBC champion Terry Norris. "I hope promoter Don King
will now force Norris to face me and when I beat him I will be
the undisputed world number one super welter," he added.
</P>
<P>
For Waters it was fifth defeat in 32 bouts and firmly puts and
end to any championship hopes he may have held.
</P>
<P>
In another fight, Mexican Ricardo Lopez defended his WBC
straw-weight title when he stopped Alexander Sanchez of Puerto
Rico in the fifth.
</P>
<P>
It was Lopez's 21st defence of his title, which he took seven
years ago, and took his record to 46-0.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old Sanchez retains his WBO crown which was not at
stake in Saturday's confrontation. 
