<HEADLINE> Large Sino-Japanese Visual Product Venture Goes Into Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Suogang Visual
Products Co. Ltd., a Sino-Japanese joint venture established with
an investment of 410 million US dollars, went into production here
recently.
</P>
<P>
The venture was established in December 1995 with joint funding
provided by Sony Corp., Sony (China) Ltd., Shanghai Video &AMP; Audio
Electronics Co. and Shanghai Vacuum Electronic Devices Co.
</P>
<P>
The venture's designed production capacity for the year 2000
will reach 1.8 million color TV sets, 1.2 million high resolution
color displays, 1.8 million color regular kinescopes and 1.2
million high resolution kinescopes.
</P>
<P>
Sony backing has enabled the venture to introduce a series of
advanced technology, including wide-screen, high-definition
television sets and multimedia techniques.
</P>
<P>
The local content ratio for products is expected to reach more
than 50 percent withing three years.
</P>
<P>
First phase construction involves the installation of three
production lines. 
</P>
