<HEADLINE> 8 Killed, 22 Injured in Bomb Explosions in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ALGIERS, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were killed and 22
others injured in two railroad explosions, informed Algerian sources
said today.
</P>
<P>
The explosions occurred Saturday while a train was traveling
from Algiers to the town of Khamis Maliana, 150 kilometers south of
the capital.
</P>
<P>
The first bomb laid on the railroad went off when the train was
running and damaged the front passenger carriage, while the second
one laid on a road near the railroad exploded a few moments after
the first blast.
</P>
<P>
Ten days ago, the Algeier-Khamis Maliana railroad also came
under a terrorist attack that injured three railroad workers.
</P>
<P>
Situation here is getting tense with the approach of the local
government election which is due to be held on October 23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
