<HEADLINE> Northwest China Airport Completes Successful Test Flight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Hedong Airport, the first
all-weather airport in Yinchuan, capital of northwest China's
Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, has completed successful test
flights and the facility will open to traffic in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the Hedong Airport, one of the country's key
projects, commenced in late 1995 and will be completed at a total
cost of 538 million yuan. The airport terminal has floor space of
over 14,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Hedong, with a projected annual handling capacity of 600,000
passengers, will regularly schedule flights to a number of
domestic and overseas locations. Completion of the facility is
expected to greatly accelerate the development of air traffic in
the region.
</P>
<P>
The airport is equipped with state-of-the-art
telecommunications and landing facilities, and has the capacity to
service all aircraft models.  
