<HEADLINE> 10 People Dead in Somali Clan Fighting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 24 (Xinhua)--Ten people were killed in clan
fighting in the self-declared Somaliland Republic over the
weekend, said a report reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The fighting on Saturday with light weapons between rival
clans in Erigabo, in the eastern region of Somaliland stemmed
from a land dispute, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Local elders and religious leaders today tried to reconcile
the two groups and restore peace to the area by separating the
rivals.
</P>
<P>
Somaliland, covering the area of the former British Somaliland
which merged with the adjoining Italian Somaliland to form an
independent republic in 1960, declared itself independent in
1991. But it has not achieved international recognition.
