<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Youth Friendship Exchange Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 24 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
and Shizuoka County in central Japan recently sponsored a four-day
youth exchange program in the provincial capital Hangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the event was to mark the 15th anniversary of the
establishment of friendship ties between the two areas, according
to Sakamot Yukiko, an education official with the Shizuoka county
government.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 Japanese middle school students visited the
Hangzhou Foreign languages School and joined local Chinese
students in a series of cultural exchange activities in areas such
as oral Chinese, calligraphy, painting, paper-cutting, music,
dancing, and sports.
</P>
<P>
They also visited a number of rural enterprises and
overseas-funded firms in Hangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The program was designed to help students learn more about the
history and culture of the two sides, and further expand
friendship between people from the two areas. 
</P>
