<HEADLINE> Michael Johnson's Entry to World Sprint Festival Uncertain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Double Olympic champion
Michael Johnson of the United States has not decided to take part in
the world sprint festival slated on August 31 at Catania, according to
the organizers of the 19th World Universiade on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Johnson, who made the history by winning both the 100 and 200
meters at one Olympic Games at Atlanta, said he didn't feel good
physically and had not made up his mind of coming to Sicily for the
sprint festival.
</P>
<P>
Primo Nebiolo, president of the IAAF and FISU, said he would
contact Johnson's manager Michelone and ask him to persude Johnson to
compete in the festival on the closing day of the Universiade.
</P>
<P>
Nebiolo said he hoped Johnson would eventually come to Catania to
show his good feeling to the Sicilian People. 
