<HEADLINE> Foreign Capital Flows to Pudong (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four functional zones have taken shape in Pudong -- the
Lujiazui Financial Trade Zone, the Jinqiao Export Processing Zone,
the Waigaoqiao Bonded Zone, and the Zhangjiang Science Park.
</P>
<P>
The fact that a dozen foreign banks have received approval to
be engaged in RMB yuan business on a trial basis is seen as a
major breakthrough in the opening-up process of the country's
financial sector.
</P>
<P>
A number of hi-tech projects have been established in the
Jinqiao and Zhangjiang zones, with Waigaoqiao emerging as a modern
foreign trade port which integrates trade with shipping.
</P>
<P>
According to official sources, Pudong will enter a new round of
investment and construction over the next few years, with some 100
billion yuan to be spent on the construction of a new
international airport, subways, new deep-water ports and
information networks.
</P>
<P>
Local experts note that Pudong will continue to improve its
infrastructure. They predict that the area will attract even more
overseas funds over the next few years.  
</P>
