<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade in Hainan Expands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Hainan, China's southernmost
island province, ended the first six months of this year with an
export volume of slightly over 554 million US dollars, up 37.8
percent on last year's same period.
</P>
<P>
The province shipped major export items, including natural gas,
and industrial and aquatics products, to a number of countries in
Southeast Asia and Europe.
</P>
<P>
Natural gas from the South China Sea, Hainan's leading export
item, gained a significant share of the international market
during the first half of the year, with one local producer alone
exporting a total of 2.84 million tons of natural gas valued at
204 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The province also witnessed steady growth in exports of
traditional items, with export earnings for timber and woodwork
products standing at 13.5 million US dollars, up 24.3 percent on
the 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
Hainan also recorded foreign exchange earnings of 10.98 million
US dollars for aquatics products and 13.5 million US dollars for
coffee and pepper.  
</P>
</TEXT>
