<HEADLINE> All Deputies to 15th National Congress of CPC Elected (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 24 (Xinhua) -- All the 2,048 deputies to the
15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) have
been elected through elections held in 36 election units across
the country.
</P>
<P>
The election unites included departments of the CPC Central
Committee, departments of the central government, the All-China
Federation of Taiwan Compatriots, the People's Liberation Army and
armed police troops, as well as 31 provinces, autonomous regions
and municipalities.
</P>
<P>
The deputies were elected at Party deputy meetings or Party
congresses through competitive elections.
</P>
<P>
The 6th Plenum of the 14th CPC Central Committee held in
October 1996 adopted the decision to convene the 15th National
Congress of the CPC in Beijing in the second half of 1997.
</P>
<P>
In November 1996, the CPC Central Committee issued a circular
on the election of the deputies to the 15th National Congress of
the CPC.
</P>
<P>
The circular spelled out specific requirements for the division
of election units, the conditions for the deputies, the
composition of the deputies, the procedures for the election of
the deputies and the allocation of the number of the deputies.
</P>
<P>
Party organizations at all levels paid close attention to the
election. In the course of discussing, nominating and electing the
deputies, the principle of democratic centralism was implemented
earnestly and democracy within the Party was carried forward
fully.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970824.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> All Deputies to 15th National Congress of CPC Elected (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Repeated consultations and discussions were held to solicit
opinions of Party organizations at all levels and Party members.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary statistics show that more than 500,000 candidates
were recommended and nominated in the first round election, and
that more than 95 percent of grass-roots Party organizations
participated in recommending the candidates, involving 85
percent of Party members.
</P>
<P>
To ensure the deputies' quality, organization departments of
Party committees at all levels made careful examinations of
candidates' political performance, moral standards, work
performance, and self-discipline and honesty. All election units
were required to have the number of candidates at least ten
percent more than that of the actual deputies elected.
</P>
<P>
The deputies to the 15th National Congress of the CPC represent
more than 58 million members of the whole Party. Of the deputies,
leading officials account for 75.9 percent; model workers,
advanced workers, outstanding experts, and heros from all walks of
life, 24.1 percent; women, 16.8 percent; people of minority ethnic
groups, 10.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, 63.5 percent of the deputies are under the age of 55,
and 83.5 percent have a college education.
</P>
<P>
The deputies who joined the Party after the founding of New
China in 1949 constitute the overwhelming majority. 
</P>
