<DOCNO> XIE19970824.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-24 08:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ceasefire Monitoring Committee Condemns Shelling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The ceasefire monitoring
committee has reached a conclusion that condemns Israel of
violating the ceasefire understanding and hurting civilians,
Lebanese radio reported this morning.
</P>
<P>
After four consecutive days of heated discussion, the
committee, which convened on Wednesday, ended its marathon
session in Naqoura on the Lebanese-Israeli border at 8:30 p.m.
(17:30 GMT) Saturday night, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
In its findings, the committee asked Israel to take
responsibility for Monday's shelling of Lebanese southern city of
Saida, which killed 9 civilians and wounded nearly 40 others.
</P>
<P>
Israel defended during the meeting that the attack was
carried out by its militia ally, the South Lebanese Army(SLA),
without knowledge of Israeli troops.
</P>
<P>
However, Lebanon insisted that the SLA's operation was under
the Israeli permission and instruction.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the committee accused Iranian-backed
Hezbollah, or Party of God, of firing Katyusha rockets at northern
Israel and the asked Lebanese government to curb this kind of
action in the future.
</P>
<P>
The committee, made up of delegates from the U.S., France,
Israel, Syria and Lebanon and established after the Israeli
16-day blitz of Lebanon in April last year, discussed 10
complaints of ceasefire violations presented by Lebanon and
Israel.
</P>
<P>
In the past five days of violence in south Lebanon, some 12
people were killed, of them, at least 10 are Lebanese
civilians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
