<HEADLINE> India May See Record Foodgrain Production: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The foodgrain production in
India this year is likely to cross a record mark of 200 million
tons, Agriculture Minister Chaturanan Mishra said here today.
</P>
<P>
According to Press Trust of India, Mishra said that the
production could even further go up if more state funds were
allocated for the agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
This year, barring certain areas in Himachal Pradesh and Bihar,
which were hit by cloudburst, the country on the whole had a good
rainfall, he said.
</P>
<P>
Taking this into account, the minister expressed hope that the
production would cross the 200 million ton mark.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that India had achieved a record foodgrain
production of 198.17 million tons last year despite all constrains
such as lack of sufficient funds.
</P>
<P>
He urged the Planning Commission to allocate more funds to the
agricultural sector for irrigation, fertilizer and seeds.
</P>
