<HEADLINE> Hakkinen Reinstated on Appeal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Finland's Mika Hakkinen of
Mclaren Mercedes has been reinstated in fifth position on the grid
for the Belgian Grand Prix after race officials accepted an appeal
by his team Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
Hakkinen had been demoted from fifth to 22nd and last on the
grid on Saturday evening after his fuel was deemed to be illegal.
</P>
<P>
A McLaren statement said the fuel had been unchanged since the
British Grand Prix, when samples from Hakkinen's car were found to
be legal.
</P>
<P>
A Mercedes spokesman said the race stewards had agreed that
further tests should be carried out next week, and that in the
meantime, Hakkinen could start the race from his qualifying
position.
</P>
<P>
McLaren sid it believed the tests would show that the fuel
would be shown to be legal.
</P>
<P>
The decision means, however, that if Hakkinen finishes the
race, the entire race result will be in doubt until the fuel
problem is resolved one way or the other. 
</P>
</TEXT>
