<HEADLINE> Dumping of Plastic Bags Banned in Haryana, India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NWQ DWLHI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Haryana state government
of India has decided to ban dumping of non-biodegradable garbage
like plastic bags into drains or on roads and open areas, the
Times of India said today.
</P>
<P>
Under a new bill adopted by the government, all offenders would
be summarily tried by a judicial magistrate.
</P>
<P>
Those found guilty would be punishable with imprisonment for a
term which may extend to one month or a fine up to 5,000 rupees
(about 143 U.S. dollars) or both.
</P>
<P>
The bill proposed to empower the local authorities to identify
sites for depositing non-biodegradable garbage and making
provisions for public depots or places for temporary collection of
non-biodegradable garbage.  
</P>
</TEXT>
