<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Starts Singaporean Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng today
arrived in Singapore, the last leg of his two-nation Southeast
Asian tour following his Malaysian visit.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier came here this morning from the Penang
State of Malaysia for a three-day official visit as guest of
Singaporean Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong.
</P>
<P>
Greeting Li at the airport included Goh, Minister of Law and
Foreign Affairs Shunmugam Jayakumar and some other senior
Singaporean officials.
</P>
<P>
A grand welcoming ceremony was held at the airport to greet the
Chinese premier upon his arrival. In Goh's company, Li reviewed
the guards of honor of the Singaporean armed forces.
</P>
<P>
In a written speech upon his arrival, Li said the Chinese and
Singaporean people enjoy a deep-rooted traditional friendship.
</P>
<P>
Since the establishment of diplomatic ties between the two
countries in 1990, Li said, "Our friendly relations and
mutually-beneficial cooperation in various fields have witnessed
rapid development."
</P>
<P>
"This is not only beneficial to the two peoples of China and
Singapore, but also an important contribution to regional peace
and stability," Li said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier also noted that China attaches importance
to the development of friendly relations with Singapore and is
willing to work with the Singaporean side to establish a
long-term, stable partnership of good-neighborliness, mutual trust
and cooperation geared towards the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Li said, "I will have in-depth exchanges of
views with Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong and other Singaporean
leaders on bilateral relations and regional and international
issues of common interest."
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that his visit will serve to further deepen
the understanding and friendship between the two governments and
peoples, and promote the development of the friendly relations and
mutually-beneficial cooperation in depth and in breadth.
</P>
<P>
Li's entourage include his wife Zhu Lin, Deputy
Secretary-General of the State Council He Chunlin, Minister of
Machine-building Industry Bao Xuding, Director of the Foreign
Affairs Office of the State Council Liu Huaqiu, Director of the
Research Office of the State Council Wang Mengkui, Vice Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan, Chinese Ambassador to Singapore Chen
Baoliu, Vice Minister in charge of the State Planning Commission
Chen Tonghai, Vice Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation Liu Shanzai, Director of the Premier's Office Jiang
Yunbao, Deputy Director of the Foreign Affairs Office of the State
Council Lu Congmin and Special Assistant Wan Jinchang.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Li is expected to confer with Goh on
promoting the Sino-Singapore relations, and on international and
regional issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Li will also meet Singaporean President Ong Teng Cheong and
Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew.
</P>
<P>
Li's last visit to Singapore was in August 1990.  
</P>
