<HEADLINE> News Briefs in Mercosur Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The following are some news
briefs in the South American Common Market (Mercosur) countries.
</P>
<P>
ASUNCION -- The foreign ministers of the Mercosur and the
Andean Pact signed an agreement to redouble their efforts to
establish a free trade area in the two blocs by the end of this
year.
</P>
<P>
A joint statement was made on August 15 during a preparatory
meeting for the 11th summit of the Group of Rio to be held on
August 23-24.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Fourteen of the 25 most profitable enterprises in
Latin America are in Mercosur countries, according to a study made
available by the Latin Trade company. The 14 companies are nine
Brazilian firms, four Argentine firms and one Chilean firm.
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- Chilean and Argentine teamsters union leaders
announced the creation of "a big confederation of Mercosur
teamsters" with more than 250,000 workers.
</P>
<P>
Jose Sandoval, president of the Chilean truck driver teamsters,
said Friday that the new labor group will seek to improve working
conditions and seek higher salaries for its members.
</P>
<P>
The confederation includes teamsters from Argentina, Brazil,
Paraguay, Uruguay and Chile, an associated country to Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil, Paraguay, Uruguay,
the United States and Venezuelas are holding joint military
maneuvers in Rio de Janeiro on August 20-29.
</P>
<P>
Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay will hold
military maneuvers next October in the Brazilian province of Rio
Grande Do Sul. The five countries held their first joint
operations in Monte Caseros in northeastern Argentina last year.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Argentina and Uruguay last Thursday signed an
agreement on sports cooperation, including exchange of human
resources and documents and cooperation between their sports
organizations.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Entrepreneurs and experts from Argentina,
Brazil, Paraguay, Uruguay and Chile took part in the 6th
International Real Estate Mercosur Congress which is held on
August 22-24 in Argentina.
</P>
<P>
They examined the possibility of unifying the rules for
buying and selling real estate, and financing for the market.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- A total of 503 Argentine and foreign exhibitors
confirmed their participation in the First International Salon of
Foods Sial-Mercosur, to be held on August 26-29 in Buenos Aires.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentina's National Administration of
Medicines, Food, and Medical Technologies has decided that
cosmetics firms in Argentina must comply with Mercosur quality
standards.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- The Institutes of Agriculture and Livestock
Research of Argentina and Brazil Thursday signed a cooperation
agreement for the exchange of technology in agriculture and
livestock.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- The Uruguayan Armed Forces Thursday started
patrolling the border with Brazil to prevent the entry of
Brazilian "landless" campesionos. Uruguayan Defense Minister Raul
Iturria said the patrolling has the approval of the Brazilian
government.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- The Soccer South American Confederation
confirmed that the Mercosur Cup will start on August 5, 1998, with
the participation of 16 teams from the group and Chile. 
</P>
