<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Arrives in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
arrived here today on a three-day official visit to Singapore, the
first by the Chinese premier since the two countries established
diplomatic relations in October 1990.
</P>
<P>
He was greeted at the airport by Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok tong.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Li is scheduled to pay a courtesy call on
Singapore President Ong Teng Cheong. He will also discuss with
Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong a wide range of international and
regional issues, as well as explore new areas of bilateral
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li will also meet with Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew
after addressing the Singapore business community Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement at Singapore's Changi International
Airport upon his arrival, Premier Li said that the Chinese and
Singapore peoples enjoy a deep-rooted traditional friendship.
</P>
<P>
"Since the establishment of diplomatic relations between China
and Singapore in 1990, our friendly relations and
mutually-beneficial cooperation in various fields have witnessed
rapid development. This is not only beneficial to the peoples of
China and Singapore, but also an important contribution to
regional peace and stability," Li stressed.
</P>
<P>
"China attaches importance to the development of friendly
relations with Singapore and is willing to work with the
Singaporean side to establish a long-term, stable partnership of
good-neighborliness, mutual trust and cooperation geared towards
the 21st century," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said he will have an in-depth exchange of views with his
Singaporean counterpart Goh Chok Tong and other Singaporean
leaders on bilateral relations and regional and international
issues of common interest.
</P>
<P>
"I hope this visit will help further deepen the understanding
and friendship between the governments and peoples of China and
Singapore and promote the development of our friendly relations
and mutually-beneficial cooperation in depth and breadth," Li
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
