<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bosnian Serb Government to Sever Relationship with Plavsic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The Bosnian Serb government
declared today that it will sever all relationship with President
Biljana Plavsic.
</P>
<P>
A government statement said the government decided not to
cooperate with the president from now on because she has refused
to abide by the ruling of the constitutional court and continued
to take actions that runs counter to the constitution.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the government will consider all her orders and
actions illegal before she takes a fair attitude toward the
constitution and returns to the administrative seat of the Serb
Republic, the Tanjug news agency of Yugoslavia said.
</P>
<P>
Plavsic dissolved parliament on July 3. In response, the Serb
government sued her on July 7 at the constitutional court, which
ruled on August 15 that the President's decision was
anti-constitutional and therefore invalid.
</P>
<P>
With the conflicts inside the Serb leading body turning
white-hot, the U.S.-led Western countries expressed overt support
for Plavsic.
</P>
<P>
On August 20, Multinational Stablization Force (SFOR) and the
International Police Task Force (IPTF) forcibly occupied the
building of the police headquarters in Banja Luka following
Plavsic's meeting with the international High Representative to
Bosnia, Carlos Westendorp, and U.S. envoy Robert Gelbard the night
before.
</P>
<P>
Two days later, Plavsic appointed Marko Pavic to replace Dragan
Kijac as the acting interior minister, prompting condemnation from
Prime Minister Gojko Klickovic, who said Plavsic's action was
anti-constitutional as the Serb constitution gives the president
no power to appoint ministers.
</P>
<P>
The General Staff of the Bosnian Serb army held an enlarged
meeting late Friday evening and raised a serious warning against
Plavsic's acts and foreign interference into Bosnia's internal
affairs.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also noted that the nation was facing a very grave
political situation.
</P>
<P>
If the situation continues to worsen, it declared, the army
will act to defend the territorial integrity and sovereignty of
the republic in line with the constitution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
