<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Reports Successful Reform in Commercial Ventures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai is trying out a
modern enterprise system in the commercial businesses, in an
effort to improve their efficiency and economic returns.
</P>
<P>
The net assets of the 30 pilot businesses climbed 17.5 percent
in the first half of this year over the same period last year,
with the asset-to-liability ratio decreasing to 70.02 percent.
</P>
<P>
The reform also lifted Shanghai's gross retail sales to
75.66 billion yuan during the January-July period, a real growth
of 16.5 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Sales of the 30 pilot businesses alone topped 28 billion yuan
for the period.
</P>
<P>
Municipal officials say that 80 percent of the commercial
ventures will be transformed into shareholding firms this year,
with two thirds of the small-sized commercial businesses
introducing a cooperative shareholding system.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai had 620 joint-stock commercial ventures and 542
cooperative shareholding commercial businesses in June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
