<HEADLINE> 2 Killed by Flood in Southern Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed by flood
as several provinces in southern Thailand remained inundated
Saturday in the wake of the tropical storm Cida, according to a
report reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Phuket, Krabi, Ranong, Surattani and Phang Nga jointed the list
of flood-hit provinces Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In Champion province alone, officials put initial damage at 57
million baht (1.7 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
In Phato district of the province, a resident was seriously
injured in a landslide while about 2,200 residents have been
evacuated to safer grounds.
</P>
<P>
The State Railway of Thailand has suspended south-bound train
service. The Asian Highway was said to be impassable Saturday as
flood water continued to rise.
</P>
<P>
Border patrol police and soldiers in these provinces were
mobilized to help rescue operations.  
</P>
