<HEADLINE> Moya, Rafter Enter New York Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Fifth seed Carlos Moya of
Spain and eighth seed Patrick Rafter of Australia today advanced
to the final of the 303,000 U.S. dollars Hamlet Cup tennis
tournament at Commack, New York.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Moya stormed past unseeded countryman Julian
Alonso, 6-2, 6-3. He needed just 51 minutes to oust Alonso.
</P>
<P>
Moya, a finalist at last week's RCA Championships in
Indianapolis of the United States, will seek his first title of
the year.
</P>
<P>
Moya also advanced to the finals at Sydney and the Australian
Open on the hard surface, and Amsterdam on clay three weeks ago.
He was seeking his third career ATP Tour title, having prevailed
at Buenos Aires in 1995 and Umag, Croatia last year.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, who also reached his second straight final today,
defeated sixth seed Thomas Enqvist of Sweden, 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old Rafter, seeded 13th, won his only title at
Manchester in 1994. However, he reached the finals at
Philadelphia, Hong Kong, Austria and last week at New Haven,
Connecticut. 
</P>
