<HEADLINE> Computerized Distribution Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Hualian Luosun Co. Ltd., a
major retailer in Shanghai, China's largest commercial center,
has introduced a computerized distribution network.
</P>
<P>
The company, which operates a chain of 24-hour convenience
shops, previously used fax communications or floppy discs for
ordering and distribution.
</P>
<P>
The new computerized network which links the company's
distribution system with its 25 retail outlets has greatly
improved efficiency for both the ordering and delivery of
goods. The move also represents a major step toward modernization
</P>
<P>
Market analysts say the pioneering reform represents a major
step forward in efforts to modernize Shanghai's commercial sector,
and has paved the way for the further development of the chain
store business. 
</P>
