<HEADLINE> Ningxia Maintains Foreign Trade Momentum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The import and export volume of
the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, northwest China, during the
first six months of this year jumped 34 percent to 109 million US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The region exported products valued at 103 million US dollars,
up 32 percent on the previous year's period, with imports growing
by 98.5 percent to 6.06 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
State foreign trade companies accounted for 63 percent of total
exports, with local trade firms adding 21 percent and
foreign-funded enterprises 16 percent.
</P>
<P>
State-owned export enterprises performed admirably following
technological transformation. Substantial growth was recorded for
exports of bearings, machine tools, chemicals and nonferrous
metals.
</P>
<P>
The region succeeded in opening new overseas markets by
sponsoring trade fairs in the United States, Argentina, Australia,
New Zealand and Hong Kong. The province has established trade ties
with 170 countries and regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
