<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Police Take Illegal Immigrants Into Custody </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Italian police detained more
illegal immigrants during regular police operations in various
parts of the country today, the ANSA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In Leece, Puglia, police operations led to the detention of 42
Albanians, including a pregnant woman.
</P>
<P>
In the northern city of Udine, 40 illegal Asian immigrants were
found. These immigrants, some from Bangladesh and Sri Lanka, were
reported in dire straits: they were exhausted, famished and
without money or identification papers.
</P>
<P>
Police suspect that they had originally arrived in Italy by
hiding in freight containers aboard ships docking in Trieste,
about 60 kilometers southeast of Udine.
</P>
<P>
Nine of the immigrants were in such bad physical shape that
they had to be taken to hospital. The Red Cross is temporarily
sheltering the others. They will all be expelled, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The detention of an increasing number of illegal immigrants has
prompted a debate in the country.
</P>
<P>
Illegal immigration was linked to mounting allegations of
violence and criminal activities in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
