<HEADLINE> Davenport Wins Atlanta Tennis Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Fourth-seeded Lindsay
Davenport of the United States beat unseeded Sandrine Testud of
France 2-0 to win the 450,000 dollars U.S. Women's Hardcourt
Championships in Atlanta on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, who won an Olympic gold medal last summer in the
same venue, breezed past Testud 6-4, 6-1 in just 59 minutes,
earning 79,000 U.S. dollars for the victory.
</P>
<P>
It was her fourth WTA Tour title this season and eleventh of
her career. She also prevailed at Oklahoma City, Indian Wells and
Amelia Island.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Davenport, who is currently the top-ranked
American-born player in women's tennis, was playing in her second
final this month. She lost to Monica Seles in the final of the
Acura Classic in Los Angeles two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
Testud, 25, who captured her first career tour title at last
month's International Tournament in Palermo, Italy, was seeking
her second title this year. 
</P>
