<HEADLINE> Schalken Wins Semifinal at Boston Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Unseeded Sjeng Schalken of
the Netherlands defeated fifth-seeded Albert Costa of Spain, 6-4,
5-7, 6-3, today to reach the final of the inaugural 303,000 U.S.
dollars MFS Pro Championships in Boston, the United States.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Schalken, who knocked off top seed Alex
Corretja of Spain on Friday, will take on the winner of tonight's
second semifinal between second-seeded Marcelo Rios of Chile and
America's Jeff Tarango.
</P>
<P>
Schalken, ranked 79th in the world, will be seeking his third
career ATP Tour title on Sunday and first of the year. He
prevailed at Valencia, Spain in 1995 and Jakarta, Indonesia in
1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
