<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, August 24 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. researchers have found in the St. Johns
River in Florida the same microorganism that exists in North
Carolina's Neuse River and Maryland's Pocomoke River, where
thousands of fish have died recently.
</P>
<P>
The dinoflagelate, which does not yet have a name in English,
was discovered by researchers from St. Petersburg's Florida Marine
Research Institute.
</P>
<P>
Scientists wonder if the one-celled organism, about the size of
a bacteria, is responsible for lesions found on fish in the
affected waterways. They have yet to learn if the microorganism is
toxic or whether it poses a public health risk. (US-Microorganism)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States will launch a scientific
spacecraft worth 111 million U.S. dollars to provide an early
warning against solar storms.
</P>
<P>
The spacecraft, which is called the Advanced Composition
Explorer(ACE), was scheduled for blast-off from Cape Canaveral Air
Station atop a Boeing Delta II rocket at 10:41 a.m. EDT on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
ACE will be positioned 1.6 million km above the Earth. It will
provide a 30 to 60 minute warning before a potentially dangerous
solar storm strikes the Earth. (US-Spacecraft)
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton said Saturday that
"fast track" approach is needed to make U.S. companies more
competitive worldwide and he will ask U.S. Congress to renew his
authority for speedy negotiation of trade agreements.
</P>
<P>
He said in his weekly radio address that 25 percent of U.S.
economic growth now comes from overseas trade, and U.S. exports
support more than 11 million "good, high-paying American jobs,"
including one of every five manufacturing positions.
(US-Clinton-Trade)
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkey will remove the 10-year-old emergency rule in
southeastern Turkey by early next year, Deputy Prime Minister
Ismet Sezgin announced Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Emergency rule will be lifted either at the end of this year
or at the start of 1998," Sezgin was quoted as saying by the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Emergency rule has been imposed in nine southeastern provinces
since 1987, giving soliders and police more extensive powers of
arrest and detention in the fight against the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK). (Turkey-Emergency Rule)
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Fighting between Israeli troops and Lebanese
Hezbullah guerrillas erupted again Saturday in south Lebanon as
the ceasefire monitoring committee is deliberating the complaints
by Israel and Lebanon of truce violations.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese official National News Agency reported that the
fighting mainly focused on the the western and central sectors of
the Israeli-established "security zone" in south Lebanon.
(Lebanon-Attack) 
</P>
</TEXT>
