<HEADLINE> Greece Tightens Traffic Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Greece has announced tougher
measures to combat rising traffic accidents in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) today,
Athens Public Prosecutor Anastasios Kanellopoulos issued a written
decree to traffic police Friday, ordering them to implement the new
measures including the confiscation of cars driven by drunk drivers
on the spot.
</P>
<P>
Under the new measures, traffic police will also confiscate
drivers' licences and plates if they are caught failing to stop at
red lights or violating other road signs.
</P>
<P>
Traffic police Friday night confiscated eight cars after the
drivers' alcohol tests proved positive.
</P>
<P>
Traffic problem has been a headache for Greece for years because
each year hundreds of people were killed and thousands injured in
road accidents across the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
