<HEADLINE> Ukraine Win Two Golds, China, United States Takes One Each </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine turned to be the
biggest winner of the day by taking two gold medals while China and
the United States snatched one each at the World Universiade on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Elena Vitrichenko took the ryhthmic individual all-around title,
the first gold for Ukraine at the 19th World University Games. Vadym
Guttsayt added one to Ukrainian tally by pocketing the men's
individual sabre title.
</P>
<P>
Hosts Italy again failed to win a gold on Saturday, but they did
manage to take a silver through Luigi Tarantino in the men's sabre as
he lost to Guttsayt 15-8 in the final.
</P>
<P>
China had a medal harvest today as their male gymnasts clean swept
the top three places in the individual all-around event.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Lihui was the surprise winner of the event after collecting a
total of 56.500 points. Zhao Sheng, the favorite before the final,
finished second at 56.000 while another Chinese gymnast Wang Dong made
a brave comeback in the last three rotations to complete China's clean
sweep of the medals.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the women's individual all-around final, American
Shannon Miller, a twice world champion and a veteran Olympian,
collected 36.937 points from four apparatus. The results was good
enough to bring her the gold medal.
</P>
<P>
Another American Kathleen Shrieves had a slow start in vault but
came back into the competitions by scoring 9.425 points in the uneven
bars. She managed to keep her slim lead over Risa Sugawara of Japan
till the final rotation and claimed the silver medal with 36.925
points.
</P>
<P>
Though Sugawara only finished with a bronze at 36.912 points, she
was the most popular athlete of the final as each time she finsihed
her performance, the spectators gave her the noisest appaluse.
</P>
<P>
The soccer tournament has a rest day on Saturday after the
conclusion of the group competitions last night. The quarter-finals
of the soccer tournament will be played at Palermo with Italy taking
on the Netherlands, China playing Ukraine, the United States meeting
Ireland and South Korea fighting against the Brazilians.
</P>
<P>
The water polo tournament of the games opened today at Palermo.
Hosts Italy were forced to a 7-7 draw by Australia while Yugoslavia
lost 7-4 to Hungary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
