<HEADLINE> China, United States Split All-around Gymnastic Golds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Italy, August 23 (Xinhua) -- China and the United States
split the men's and women's individual all-around gold medals in the
gymnastic competiton of the 19th World University Games at the Sports
Center here on Saturday evening.
</P>
<P>
Chinese men gymnasts came from behind to win all three medals.
Zheng Lizhi scored 56.050 points for the champion. zhao sheng and
Wang Dong took the silver and bronze medals with respective socres of
56.000 points and 55.900 points.
</P>
<P>
36 participants from 19 countries competed in the men's event.
</P>
<P>
Duan Shijie, head of the Chinese sports delegation, said with
pleasure: "we are satisfied with our gymnasts' performence this
evening."
</P>
<P>
Xiao Yinchun, coach of the Chinese team, said that our men gymnasts
performed well. But the young athletes should improve their skill and
technique so as to achieve better results in further international
tournaments.
</P>
<P>
In the women's competition, American Shannon Miller, Atlanta
Olympic beam gold medallist and two-time all-around chamion at the past
world championships, snatched the gold medal by collecting a total of
36.937 points in the floor, beam, uneven bars and vault events.
</P>
<P>
Her compatriot Kathleen Shrievens got the silver medal with 36.925
points while Japanese Risa Sugawara came third with 36.912 points.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Rozalia Galieva who ranked first with 37.125 points after
the women's team competition on Friday, withdrew from today's contest
because She injured yesterday during the exercise at beam, a press
release said.
</P>
<P>
In today's individual all-around rhythmic gymnastic competition,
Ukrainean Elena Vitrichenko totalled 39.732 points in the rope, club,
ribbon and hoop events to win the gold medal. The winner gained top
point of ten in the ribbon competition.
</P>
<P>
Tatiana Orgyzko of belarus took the silver medal with 39.698 points
and Amina Zaripova of Russia came third with 39.506 points.
</P>
<P>
The rhythmic gymnastic competition will produce four gold medals
for the aparatus finals on Sunday and on the same day gymnasts will
compete for 10 golds in the men's and women's individual events.
</P>
</TEXT>
